    "notes": "Phase 2 curated 2026-05-29 under curation-data-contract (Tier 1 host #1, rewrite of the rolled-back Delta Pav template). Radius/Teff/luminosity anchored on Rains et al. 2020 VLTI/PIONIER direct interferometry (theta_LD = 1.828 +/- 0.025 mas -> R 1.197 +/- 0.016 Rsun, Teff 5571 +/- 48 K, L 1.24 +/- 0.03 Lsun); the prior synthesis used Bruntt 2010 asteroseismic R and Gaia GSP-Phot Teff and falsely assumed no interferometry (dec -66 is reachable by VLTI/SUSI, only CHARA/NPOI cannot). Rains cross-checks Bruntt 2010 asteroseismic R 1.20 / L 1.22 within 1 sigma; the prior md mislabeled Bruntt's luminosity (1.22) as radius. Mass = Bruntt 2010 asteroseismology 1.07 +/- 0.13 (no binary orbit; Lund et al. 2025 TESS gives modern nu_max 2269.8 / Delta_nu 107.9 uHz but no published modeled M/R). [Fe/H] = Gomes da Silva 2021 AMBRE-HARPS +0.36 +/- 0.02 (Bensby 2014 +0.37, Bruntt 2010 +0.33 corroborate). Activity = Gomes da Silva 2021 HARPS log R'HK -5.13 (replaces Henry 1996 -4.999; very inactive old subgiant); Hunsch 1998 ROSAT log(Lx/Lbol) ~ -6.4. Age is a DOCUMENTED DIVERGENCE: Holmberg 2009 GCS III isochrone 9.3 Gyr (range 5.8-10.7) recommended as consistent with the very low activity + slow rotation, vs Bensby 2014 isochrone 4.9 Gyr (range 3.3-9.6); ranges overlap 5.8-9.6 -- Phase 3 must document this. Rotation: only v sin i ~ 1.7 km/s (Bruntt 2010) -> P_rot <~ 36 d (sin i upper bound); no measured period, so not recorded as a rotation_measurement. Gaia DR3 GSP-Phot/FLAME rejected (Teff 5437, [Fe/H] +0.03, age 0.59 Gyr biased for this bright metal-rich star)."
